nt political struggle between Russia and the West as being in part a conflict between the liberal West and an illiberal Russia. By explaining the historical causes of liberalism's failure in that country, Russian Liberalism offers an understanding of a significant aspect of contemporary international affairs. After Putin's February 2022 invasion of Ukraine, understanding Russian political thought is a matter of considerable importance.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aLiberalismzRussia (Federation). 0aLiberalismzRussia. 0aLiberalismzSoviet Union. 0aPolitical culturezRussia (Federation). 0aPolitical culturezRussia. 0aPolitical culturezSoviet Union. 4aHISTORY. 4aPolitical Science & Political History. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / World / Russian & Former Soviet Union.2bisacsh  aliberalism in Russia, russian goverments, goverment opossion in Russian, russian political spectrum, russian political parties, russian liberals.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311075183340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781501772160?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501772160423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501772160/original  a978-3-11-075183-3  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles